cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.MM, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with information theory and coding for a specific type of coding system, the Slepian-Wolf coding system. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with the encoding and decoding of correlated sources, which falls under the sub-category cs.SI (Signal Processing). The assumption of stationary memoryless sources and the use of probability mass functions suggest that the paper could also be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with achievable rate regions, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category as well.
